problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/ransom-note/description/
Intuition
To determine whether the ransom note can be constructed , i first count the freq of each required charcater in the rasnom note using hash map ,

I also maintain another hash map to store the freq of charcaters encountered while traversing the magazine , whenever the freq of a character in magazine matches its required freq in ransom note , i increment a vraiable have.

The varibale required represents the number of unique charcaters that must satisfy the required frequencies, if have becomes equal to required , it means every required charcater has beeen found , in sufficient quantity so i return True , if the traversal of the magazine finishes before all required frequencies are satisfied i return false.

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n+m) :
n = length of ransomNote
m = length of magazine
Building the target frequency map takes O(n), and traversing the magazine takes O(m).

Space complexity:
O(k)

Where k is the number of distinct characters stored in the hash maps.
Since the problem contains only lowercase English letters, the auxiliary space is effectively O(1).

Code
class Solution:
    def canConstruct(self, ransomNote: str, magazine: str) -> bool:
        target = {}
        for ch in ransomNote:
            target[ch] = target.get(ch,0) + 1
        required = len(target)
        freq = {}
        have = 0
        for ch in magazine:
            freq[ch] = freq.get(ch,0) + 1
            if ch in target and freq[ch] == target[ch]:
                have += 1
            if have == required:
                return True
        return False
